#. type: Content of: <sect1><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:8
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:15
msgid "Using GRUB to Set Up the Boot Process with UEFI"
msgstr "Utiliser GRUB pour paramétrer le processus de démarrage avec UEFI"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect1info>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:12
msgid "<date>$Date$</date>"
msgstr "<date>$Date$</date>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:18
msgid "Turn Off Secure Boot"
msgstr "Désactiver le Secure Boot"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:21
#| msgid ""
#| "BLFS does not have the essential packages to support Secure Boot. To set up "
#| "the boot process with GRUB for UEFI installed in BLFS, Secure Boot must be "
#| "turned off from the configuration interface of the firmware.  Read the "
#| "documentation provided by the manufacturer of your system to find out how."
msgid ""
"BLFS does not have the essential packages to support Secure Boot. To set up "
"the boot process with GRUB and UEFI in BLFS, Secure Boot must be turned off "
"from the configuration interface of the firmware.  Read the documentation "
"provided by the manufacturer of your system to find out how."
msgstr ""
"BLFS ne propose pas les paquets essentiels pour prendre en charge Secure "
"Boot. Pour paramétrer le processus de démarrage avec GRUB et UEFI dans BLFS,"
" Secure Boot doit être désactivé dans l'interface de configuration du "
"micrologiciel. Lisez la documentation fournie par le fabriquant de votre "
"système pour trouver comment faire."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:30
msgid "Create an Emergency Boot Disk"
msgstr "Créer un disque de démarrage d'urgence"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:33
msgid ""
"Ensure that an emergency boot disk is ready to <quote>rescue</quote> the "
"system in case the system becomes un-bootable.  To make an emergency boot "
"disk with GRUB for an EFI based system, find a spare USB flash drive and "
"create a <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> file system on "
"it.  Install <xref linkend=\"dosfstools\"/> first, then as the <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user:"
msgstr ""
"Assurez-vous qu'un disque de démarrage d'urgence est prêt pour "
"<quote>secourir</quote> le système au cas où le système ne puisse démarrer. "
"Pour créer un disque de démarrage d'urgence avec GRUB pour un système EFI, "
"trouvez un clé USB libre et créez un système de fichiers <systemitem "
"class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> dessus. Installez d'abord <xref "
"linkend=\"dosfstools\"/>, puis en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:44
msgid ""
"The following command will erase all directories and files in the partition."
"  Make sure your USB flash drive contains no data which will be needed, and "
"change <userinput>sdx1</userinput> to the device node corresponding to the "
"first partition of the USB flash drive.  Be careful not to overwrite your "
"hard drive with a typo!"
msgstr ""
"La commande suivante supprimera tous les répertoires et fichiers de la "
"partition. Assurez-vous que votre clé USB ne contient aucune donnée requise,"
" et remplacez <userinput>sdx1</userinput> par le nœud de périphérique "
"correspondant à la première partition de la clé USB. Faites attention à ne "
"pas écraser votre disque dur à cause d'une coquille&nbsp;!"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:52
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>mkfs.vfat /dev/sdx1</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>mkfs.vfat /dev/sdx1</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:55
msgid ""
"Still as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, use the "
"<command>fdisk</command> utility to set the first partition of the USB flash"
" drive to be an <quote>EFI system</quote> partition (change "
"<userinput>sdx</userinput> to the device node corresponding to your USB "
"flash drive):"
msgstr ""
"Toujours en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, utilisez l'utilitaire "
"<command>fdisk</command> pour faire de la première partition de la clé USB "
"une partition <quote>EFI system</quote> (remplacez "
"<userinput>sdx</userinput> par le nœud de périphérique correspondant à votre"
" clé USB)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:62
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>fdisk /dev/sdx</userinput>\n"
"<literal>\n"
"Welcome to fdisk (util-linux 2.38.1).\n"
"Changes will remain in memory only, until you decide to write them.\n"
"Be careful before using the write command.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Command (m for help): </literal><userinput>t</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Partition number (1-9, default 9): </literal><userinput>1</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Partition type or alias (type L to list all): </literal><userinput>uefi</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Changed type of partition 'Linux filesystem' to 'EFI System'.\n"
"\n"
"Command (m for help): </literal><userinput>w</userinput>\n"
"<literal>The partition table has been altered.\n"
"Calling ioctl() to re-read partition table.\n"
"Syncing disks.</literal>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>fdisk /dev/sdx</userinput>\n"
"<literal>\n"
"Welcome to fdisk (util-linux 2.38.1).\n"
"Changes will remain in memory only, until you decide to write them.\n"
"Be careful before using the write command.\n"
"\n"
"\n"
"Command (m for help): </literal><userinput>t</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Partition number (1-9, default 9): </literal><userinput>1</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Partition type or alias (type L to list all): </literal><userinput>uefi</userinput>\n"
"<literal>Changed type of partition 'Linux filesystem' to 'EFI System'.\n"
"\n"
"Command (m for help): </literal><userinput>w</userinput>\n"
"<literal>The partition table has been altered.\n"
"Calling ioctl() to re-read partition table.\n"
"Syncing disks.</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:80
msgid ""
"Still as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create a"
" mount point for the EFI partition on the USB flash drive and mount it:"
msgstr ""
"Toujours en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, créez un point de montage pour la "
"partition EFI sur la clé USB et montez-la&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:85
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /mnt/rescue &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 /mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /mnt/rescue &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sdx1 /mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:89
msgid "Install GRUB for EFI on the partition:"
msgstr "Installez GRUB pour EFI sur la partition&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:92
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable --efi-"
"directory=/mnt/rescue --boot-directory=/mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>grub-install --target=x86_64-efi --removable --efi-"
"directory=/mnt/rescue --boot-directory=/mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:95
msgid "Unmount the partition:"
msgstr "Démontez la partition&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:98
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>umount /mnt/rescue</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>umount /mnt/rescue</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:101
#| msgid ""
#| "Now the USB flash drive can be used as a emergency boot disk on x86-64 UEFI "
#| "platform.  It will boot the system and show the GRUB shell.  Then you can "
#| "type commands to boot your operating systems on the hard drive.  To learn "
#| "how to select the boot device, read the manual of your motherboard or "
#| "laptop."
msgid ""
"Now the USB flash drive can be used as an emergency boot disk on any x86-64 "
"UEFI platform.  It will boot the system and show the GRUB shell.  Then you "
"can type commands to boot your operating system from the hard drive.  To "
"learn how to select the boot device, read the manual of your motherboard or "
"laptop."
msgstr ""
"Maintenant vous pouvez utiliser la clé USB comme un disque de démarrage "
"d'urgence sur la plateforme UEFI x86-64. Elle démarrera le système et "
"affichera le shell de GRUB. Ensuite vous pourrez taper des commandes pour "
"démarrer votre système d'exploitation sur votre disque dur. Pour apprendre à"
" choisir le périphérique de démarrage, lisez le manuel de votre carte mère "
"ou de votre ordinateur portable."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:111
msgid "Kernel Configuration for UEFI support"
msgstr "Configuration du noyau pour la prise en charge de l'UEFI"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:114
msgid ""
"Enable the following options in the kernel configuration and recompile the "
"kernel if necessary:"
msgstr ""
"Activez les options suivantes dans la configuration du noyau et recompilez "
"le noyau si nécessaire&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:118
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<literal>Processor type and features ---&gt;\n"
