"File systems ---&gt;\n"
"  &lt;DOS/FAT/EXFAT/NT Filesystems ---&gt;\n"
"    &lt;*/M&gt; VFAT (Windows-95) fs support                         [CONFIG_VFAT_FS]\n"
"  Pseudo filesystems ---&gt;\n"
"    &lt;*/M&gt; EFI Variable filesystem                              [CONFIG_EFIVAR_FS]</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:144
#| msgid "The meaning of the configure options:"
msgid "The meaning of the configuration options:"
msgstr "Voici la signification des options de configuration&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:147
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_STUB</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_STUB</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:149
msgid ""
"Although the EFI stub is designed to boot a kernel directly from the UEFI "
"firmware (without a bootloader like GRUB), GRUB needs the kernel to be "
"loaded to support the EFI handover protocol enabled by this option."
msgstr ""
"Bien que le bout EFI soit conçu pour démarrer un noyau directement à partir "
"du micrologiciel UEFI (sans un chargeur d'amorçage comme GRUB), GRUB a "
"besoin que le noyau soit chargé pour prendre en charge le protocole de "
"passage de relai autorisé par cette option."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:157
msgid "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_VARS</parameter>"
msgstr "<parameter>CONFIG_EFI_VARS</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:159
msgid ""
"Don't use this deprecated option because of a 1024-byte variable size limit."
"  Its function is replaced by <parameter>CONFIG_EFIVAR_FS</parameter>."
msgstr ""
"N'utilisez pas cette option obsolète à cause d'une limite de taille à 1024 "
"octets. Elle est remplacée par <parameter>CONFIG_EFIVAR_FS</parameter>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><term>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:167
#| msgid ""
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_SYSFB_SIMPLEFB</parameter>, "
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_DRM</parameter>, <parameter>CONFIG_SIMPLEDRM</parameter>, "
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_FB</parameter>, and "
#| "<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"
msgid ""
"<parameter>CONFIG_SYSFB_SIMPLEFB</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM_SIMPLEDRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FB</parameter>, and "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"
msgstr ""
"<parameter>CONFIG_SYSFB_SIMPLEFB</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_DRM_SIMPLEDRM</parameter>, "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FB</parameter> et "
"<parameter>CONFIG_FRAMEBUFFER_CONSOLE</parameter>"

#. type: Content of:
#. <sect1><sect2><variablelist><varlistentry><listitem><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:173
#| msgid ""
#| "The combination of these options allows the kernel to print debug messages "
#| "(along with Tux logos) at the early stage of the boot process with UEFI.  To"
#| " ensure them functional at the early stage, they shouldn't be built as a "
#| "kernel module unless an initramfs will be used."
msgid ""
"The combination of these options allows the kernel to print debug messages "
"(along with Tux logos) at an early stage of the boot process with UEFI.  To "
"ensure they are functional at that early stage, they shouldn't be built as "
"kernel modules unless an initramfs will be used."
msgstr ""
"La combinaison de ces options permet au noyau d'afficher des messages de "
"débogage (avec les logos de Tux) pendant les premières étapes du processus "
"de démarrage avec UEFI. Pour vous assurer qu'ils seront fonctionnels pendant"
" ces premières étapes, ils ne doivent pas être construits en tant que "
"modules du noyau à moins que vous n'utilisiez un initramfs."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:186
msgid "Find or Create the EFI System Partition"
msgstr "Trouver ou créer la partition EFI système"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:189
#| msgid ""
#| "On EFI based system, the bootloaders are installed in a special FAT32 "
#| "partition called an <emphasis>EFI System Partition</emphasis> (ESP).  If "
#| "your system supports EFI, and a recent version of Linux distribution or "
#| "Windows is pre-installed, it's likely that the ESP is already created.  As "
#| "the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, list all the "
#| "partitions on your hard drive (replace <userinput>sda</userinput> with the "
#| "device corresponding to the appropriate hard drive):"
msgid ""
"On EFI based systems, the bootloaders are installed in a special FAT32 "
"partition called an <emphasis>EFI System Partition</emphasis> (ESP).  If "
"your system supports EFI, and a recent version of some Linux distribution or"
" Windows is pre-installed, it's likely that the ESP has already been "
"created.  As the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, list"
" all the partitions on your hard drive (replace <userinput>sda</userinput> "
"with the device corresponding to the appropriate hard drive):"
msgstr ""
"Sur les systèmes EFI, les chargeurs d'amorçage sont installés dans une "
"partition FAT32 spéciale appelée <emphasis>partition EFI système</emphasis> "
"(ESP). Si votre système prend EFI en charge, et qu'une version récente de "
"Linux ou Windows est pré-installée, il est probable que l'ESP soit déjà "
"créée. En tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, listez toutes les partitions de votre "
"disque dur (remplacez <userinput>sda</userinput> par le périphérique "
"correspondant au disque dur approprié)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:199
#, no-wrap
msgid "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"
msgstr "<userinput>fdisk -l /dev/sda</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:202
msgid ""
"The <quote>Type</quote> column of the ESP should be <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."
msgstr ""
"La colonne <quote>Type</quote> de l'ESP devrait être <literal>EFI "
"System</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:207
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "If the system or the hard drive is new, or it's a first time install an UEFI"
#| " booted OS on the system, the ESP may not exist.  In that case, create a new"
#| " partition, make a <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> file "
#| "system on it, and set the partition type to <quote>EFI system</quote>.  See "
#| "the instructions for the emergency boot device above as a reference."
msgid ""
"If the system or the hard drive is new, or it's the first installation of a "
"UEFI-booted OS on the system, the ESP may not exist.  In that case, create a"
" new partition, make a <systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> "
"file system on it, and set the partition type to <quote>EFI system</quote>."
"  See the instructions for the emergency boot device above as a reference."
msgstr ""
"Si le système ou le disque dur est neuf, ou si c'est la première "
"installation d'un système UEFI sur le système, l'ESP n'existe peut-être pas."
" Dans ce cas, créez une nouvelle partition, mettez un système de fichier "
"<systemitem class=\"filesystem\">vfat</systemitem> dessus et indiquez "
"<quote>EFI system</quote> comme type de partition. Voir les instructions sur"
" le périphérique de démarrage d'urgence plus haut pour référence."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><warning><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:217
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "Some (old) UEFI implementations may demand the ESP to be the first partition"
#| " on the disk."
msgid ""
"Some (old) UEFI implementations may require the ESP to be the first "
"partition on the disk."
msgstr ""
"Certaines (vieilles) implémentations UEFI peuvent demander que l'ESP soit la"
" première partition du disque."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:223
msgid ""
"Now, as the <systemitem class=\"username\">root</systemitem> user, create "
"the mount point for the ESP, and mount it (replace "
"<userinput>sda1</userinput> with the device node corresponding to the ESP):"
msgstr ""
"Maintenant, en tant qu'utilisateur <systemitem "
"class=\"username\">root</systemitem>, créez le point de montage pour l'ESP "
"et montez-la (remplacez <userinput>sda1</userinput> par le nœud de "
"périphérique correspondant à l'ESP)&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:229
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mkdir -pv /boot/efi &amp;&amp;\n"
"mount -v -t vfat /dev/sda1 /boot/efi</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:233
msgid ""
"Add an entry for the ESP in <filename>/etc/fstab</filename>, so it will be "
"mounted automatically during system boot:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutez une entrée pour l'ESP dans <filename>/etc/fstab</filename> pour "
"qu'elle soient montée automatiquement au démarrage du système&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
