msgid ""
"<literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal>, and "
"<literal>5.19.2-lfs-11.2</literal> must match your configuration."
msgstr ""
"Vous devez remplacer <literal>(hd0,2)</literal>, <literal>sda2</literal> et "
"<literal>5.19.2-lfs-r11.2</literal> pour correspondre à votre configuration."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><note><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:493
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "From GRUB's perspective, the files are relative to the partition are used. "
#| "If you used a separate /boot partition, remove /boot from the above paths "
#| "(to kernel and to <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>). You will also need to "
#| "change the set root line to point to the boot partition."
msgid ""
"From GRUB's perspective, the files are relative to the partitions used. If "
"you used a separate /boot partition, remove /boot from the above paths (to "
"kernel and to <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>). You will also need to "
"change the \"set root\" line to point to the boot partition."
msgstr ""
"Du point de vu de GRUB, les fichiers sont relatifs à la partition utilisée. "
"Si vous utilisez une partition /boot séparée, supprimez /boot dans les "
"chemins précédents (vers le noyau et vers <filename>unicode.pf2</filename>)."
" Vous devrez aussi changer la ligne set root pour pointer vers la partition "
"de démarrage."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:502
msgid ""
"The <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> entry can be used to enter the "
"configuration interface provided by the firmware (sometimes called "
"<quote>BIOS configuration</quote>)."
msgstr ""
"L'entrée <literal>Firmware Setup</literal> peut être utilisée pour entrer "
"dans l'interface de configuration fournie par le micrologiciel (parfois "
"nommée <quote>configuration BIOS</quote>)."

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><title>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:509
msgid "Dual-booting with Windows"
msgstr "Démarrage double avec Windows"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:512
msgid "Add a menu entry for Windows into <filename>grub.cfg</filename>:"
msgstr ""
"Ajoutew une entrée de menu pour Windows dans "
"<filename>grub.cfg</filename>&nbsp;:"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><screen>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:515
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 11\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>cat &gt;&gt; /boot/grub/grub.cfg &lt;&lt; EOF</userinput>\n"
"<literal># Begin Windows addition\n"
"\n"
"menuentry \"Windows 11\" {\n"
"  insmod fat\n"
"  insmod chain\n"
"  set root=(hd0,1)\n"
"  chainloader /EFI/Microsoft/Boot/bootmgfw.efi\n"
"}</literal>\n"
"<userinput>EOF</userinput>"

#. type: Content of: <sect1><sect2><para>
#: blfs-en/postlfs/filesystems/uefi-bootloaders/grub-setup.xml:527
#, fuzzy
#| msgid ""
#| "<literal>(hd0,1)</literal> should be replaced with the GRUB designated name "
#| "for the ESP.  The <literal>chainloader</literal> directive can be used to "
#| "tell GRUB to run another EFI executable, in this case the Windows Boot "
#| "Manager. You may put more usable tools in EFI executable format (for "
#| "example, an EFI shell) into the ESP and create GRUB entries for them."
msgid ""
"<literal>(hd0,1)</literal> should be replaced with the GRUB designated name "
"for the ESP.  The <literal>chainloader</literal> directive can be used to "
"tell GRUB to run another EFI executable, in this case the Windows Boot "
"Manager. You may put more usable tools in EFI executable format (for "
"example, an EFI shell) into the ESP and create GRUB entries for them, as "
"well."
msgstr ""
"Vous devriez remplacer <literal>(hd0,1)</literal> par le nom désigné par "
"GRUB pour l'ESP. Vous pouvez utiliser la directive "
"<literal>chainloader</literal> pour dire à GRUB de lancer un autre "
"exécutable EFI, dans ce cas le gestionnaire de démarrage de Windows. Vous "
"pouvez ajouter des outils supplémentaires au format exécutable EFI (par "
"exemple un shell EFI) dasn l'ESP et leur créer des entrées GRUB."

